I don't know what's going on here but I have read over the posting's of a guy who calls himself doc spatz.  I generally don't have time to browse but I had a few spare moments and visited this site.  I take it that this spatz claims to be some kind of counselor.  If he is he is decidely unethical and the place that employs him is also unethical.  He has a problem that jumps out at you from everything he says. Pity his patients.  He has a problem with the many millions of Vietnam Veterans of which I happened to be one.  I was a Navy Corpsman attached to the GRUNTS. He said that the people who went to Vietnam were the poor, the uneducated etc..  Well I would like to say that I have a Doctorate in History and am a professor at a large southern college(I suppose he'll have something to say about the South) and am educated.  I can also write without using the well known four letter words.  You other guys cannot talk  to someone like this guy in a rational discourse so let him go.  In the scheme of things he's not important.  The important thing is what you did for yourself and your friends in Vietnam when you were there.  Welcome home and Semper Fi.
